1.00	Shiah_Islam	Shia Islam	Shia Islam (Arabic: ‎, Shīʿah, singular/adjective form is Shi'i (Arabic: شيعي‎)) is the second largest denomination of Islam. The followers of Shia Islam are called Shi'ites or Shias. "Shia" is the short form of the historic phrase Shīʻatu ʻAlī (), meaning "followers of Ali", "faction of Ali", or "party of Ali".	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f2/ImamHusaynMosqueKarbalaIraqPre2006.JPG/220px-ImamHusaynMosqueKarbalaIraqPre2006.JPG
